						<div class="postbody">Haha, nifty implementation of a variable-width int. I wouldn't have thought of using a bitfield in a template like that, but it's perfect.
<br />
<br />BTW, I noticed that the Wiki page was in fact in error. It described the LFSR as if it only had 14 bits (pus a 15th extra temporary bit). I've corrected it, and clarified how it only has 15 bits in actuality, even though 16 are used in the description of shifting.</div>

